{"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Keys","anchor":"Keys","identifiers":["doc:\/\/NordicMesh\/documentation\/NordicMesh\/ApplicationKey","doc:\/\/NordicMesh\/documentation\/NordicMesh\/Security","doc:\/\/NordicMesh\/documentation\/NordicMesh\/Key","doc:\/\/NordicMesh\/documentation\/NordicMesh\/KeyIndex","doc:\/\/NordicMesh\/documentation\/NordicMesh\/KeyRefreshPhase","doc:\/\/NordicMesh\/documentation\/NordicMesh\/KeyRefreshPhaseTransition"],"generated":true}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/NordicMesh\/documentation\/NordicMesh\/NetworkKey"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:10NordicMesh10NetworkKeyC","modules":[{"name":"NordicMesh"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"NetworkKey","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"NetworkKey","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"NetworkKey","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Class","symbolKind":"class"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/NordicMesh\/documentation\/NordicMesh"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"NetworkKey"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/NordicMesh\/documentation\/NordicMesh\/Exporting"]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A Network Key defines a subnet within the mesh network. Knowing the Network Key"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is required to decrypt the message, handle it, or relay. Messages can only be relayed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"within the subnet."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each key is identified by a "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/NordicMesh\/documentation\/NordicMesh\/KeyIndex"},{"type":"text","text":". There can be up to 4095 subnets in a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"mesh network."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The key is 128-bit long. Cryptographic algorithms are used to derive a Network ID, the NID","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and a set of keys used for for encrypting different types of messages:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Identity Key"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Beacon Key","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Private Beacon Key"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Encryption Key"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Privacy Key","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The key can be changed. Changing the Network Key is a secure way of removing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Nodes from a mesh network. The procedure of changing a Network Key is called"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Key Refresh Procedure (KRP). Nodes that are not part of KRP are effectively"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"excluded from the mesh network and may no longer send messages on given subnet."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A key may be either secure or insecure. A key is considered secure if all Nodes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that know this key have been provisioned in a secure way, that is using Out-Of-Band","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Public Key. Any other way of provisioning devices makes the Network Key insecure.","type":"text"}]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/nordicmesh\/networkkey"]}],"top